d Hoffnung / The Berlin Palace: Desire, Denial and Hope -- tUn-Erhörte Ideen / Unheard(-of) Ideas -- tPROJEKTE / PROJECTS -- tEPILOG -- tANHANG / APPENDIX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIm Jahr 2018 ist Deutschland 28 Jahre vereint, exakt so lange, wie die innerdeutsche Mauer bestand hatte (1961-1989). Im Deutschen Pavillon der Architekturbiennale 2018 in Venedig nehmen GRAFT Architekten Lars Krückeberg, Wolfram Putz und Thomas Willemeit gemeinsam mit der Politikerin Marianne Birthler diese Zeitengleiche zum Anlass, die Auswirkungen von Teilung und den Prozess der Heilung als dynamisches, räumliches Phänomen zu untersuchen. Die begleitende Publikation legt das Augenmerk auf herausragende stadträumliche und architektonische Beispiele der ehemaligen innerdeutschen Mauer, die sich mit Trennung und Zusammenwachsen auseinandersetzen. Ein Schwerpunkt liegt dabei auf der ehemaligen Berliner Mauer. Zahlreiche Essays namhafter Architekten, Städtebauer und Politologen widmen sich den urbanen Ausprägungen dieser Entwicklung, die sich auch andernorts zeigt.  aIn 2018, Germany will have been unified for 28 years, which is exactly as long as the inner German border existed (1961–1989). In the German Pavilion at the 2018 Architecture Biennale in Venice, GRAFT Architects Lars Krückeberg, Wolfram Putz and Thomas Willemeit, together with German politician Marianne Birthler investigate the effects of the separation and the process of healing as dynamic, spatial phenomena. The accompanying publication focuses on outstanding urban design and architectural examples of the former inner German border that engage with the issues of separation and fusion. One focus is on the former Berlin Wall. Numerous essays by architects, urban designers, and political scientists examine the urban manifestations of this development, which can also be seen elsewhere.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aArchitecturexPolitical aspectszGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aArchitecturexPolitical aspectszGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 0aBerlin Wall, Berlin, Germany, 1961-1989. 0aNationalism and architecture. 0aWalls. 4aAbgrenzung. 4aArchitektur. 4aMauer. 4aProtektionismus. 4aSpaltung. 4aStädtebau. 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh  a- architecture - ubanism - protectionism - division - walls - boundaries.1 aArchitekten, GRAFT, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBirthler, Marianne , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBirthler, Marianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCramer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElworthy, Scilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeireiss, Kristin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlausmeier, Axel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKornblum, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrückeberg, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPilz, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPutz, Wolfram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStimmann, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTiefensee, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWillemeit, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTit